      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the potatoes<strong> </strong>are almost fork-tender, add the <strong>haddock bites </strong>(unevenly sized haddock bites? Chop any larger ones into bite-sized pieces!), <strong>spinach</strong> and <strong>soft cheese</strong> to the potatoes and season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Cook for 4-5 min or until the haddock is cooked through and the potatoes are fork-tender – this is your <strong>curried haddock, leek & potato chowder</strong></p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked when it turns opaque and flakes easily</p>",
